Package: causatr
Title: Unified Causal Effect Estimation for Methodological Triangulation
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Lorenzo", "Fabbri", , "lorenzo.fabbri92sm@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-3031-322X"))
Description: Estimates causal effects via g-computation, inverse probability
    weighting, and matching for methodological triangulation. Primary engine
    is the parametric g-formula and iterated conditional expectation (ICE)
    g-computation with empirical sandwich variance estimation. Ships a
    self-contained density-ratio IPW engine and delegates matching to
    MatchIt. Supports binary, continuous,
    categorical, and multivariate treatments (multivariate is g-computation
    only); static, dynamic, modified treatment, and stochastic interventions
    (stochastic is g-computation only); continuous, binary, count
    (Poisson, negative binomial), quasibinomial (fractional), Gamma,
    and beta regression outcomes; and external observation weights. Longitudinal data is handled via ICE
    g-computation. Survival analysis and competing risks are scaffolded;
    cluster-robust variance beyond matching subclasses is planned.
Date: 2026-04-14
